<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[869,1494,314,595]" lastBlockId="9.[94,719,218,595]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,1137,314,339]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
Pronotum with broad median brown strip from anterior to posterior margins, laterally bordered by one yellow strip each side from anterior to posterior angles; elytra entirely brown; males: fore femur with blunt tooth near apex, notched beyond the apical fourth; aedeagus with right prolongation of tegmen narrowed apically and markedly oblique, separated from left setiferous prolongation by a broad and straight notch; left setiferous prolongation elongate, slender, with few short apical setae; females: ventrite VII trapezoidal, distal margin projected, notched medially.
</paragraph>
