<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[94,719,634,1075]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[94,341,634,659]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description: Length:</emphasis>
<quantity box="[353,485,634,659]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="7.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="8.3" valueMax="8.9" valueMin="7.7">7.7-8.9 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[500,648,634,659]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Colouration:</emphasis>
Head black. Maxillary palpi yellow, last palpomere apically infuscate. Antennae brown, antennomeres I-II and base of III testaceous, apico-dorsally infuscate. Pronotum with a broad median brown strip from anterior to posterior margins, laterally bordered by yellow strip each side, from anterior to posterior angles. Scutellum and elytra brown. Legs bicolour, coxae and trochanters yellow, femora yellow dorsally, covered with elongate brown strip on distal half, tibiae and tarsi brownish. Abdomen black (
<figureCitation box="[643,707,922,947]" captionStart="Figures 1-6" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1356,206,2041]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[151,1360,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 1-6:Dorsal habitus ofMacromalthinus species.(1) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(2)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(3)M.orapuensis sp.nov.(4) M.piceiventrissp.nov. (5) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(6)M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384149/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). A male 
<typeStatus box="[179,279,954,979]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">paratype</typeStatus>
has a lighter colour scheme, pronotum yellow with dark-brown patch anteriorly, legs mostly yellow. One female 
<typeStatus box="[284,384,1018,1043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">paratype</typeStatus>
from Petite Montagne Tortue has a darker colour pattern, with pronotum brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[94,719,1114,1395]" lastBlockId="9.[794,1419,218,1107]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[94,159,1114,1139]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Male:</emphasis>
Head 1.22 times wider than pronotum; temples elongate, tapering posteriorly; frons depressed between eyes. Eyes developed, convex, internal margins convergent anteriorly. Antennae thin, slender, first antennomere dilated, 3.2 times longer than broad, following not compressed. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[457,519,1274,1299]" captionStart="Figures 7-12" captionStartId="4.[869,937,1217,1242]" captionTargetBox="[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-697@4.[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 7-12: Pronotum of Macromalthinus species. (7) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (8) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (9) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (10) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (11) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (12) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384151/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) 1.12 times wider than long; anterior margin arched, posterior margin rounded medially, sinuate near angles. Lateral margins straight, regularly narrowing anteriorly; margins thinly bordered, stronger near anterior and posterior angles; pronotal surface dull, not punctate, with a thin, whitish pubescence. Elytra short, thinly punctate, slightly wrinkled, covered with thin yellowish setae, obliquely bent backwards; sutures dehiscent from anterior third; apex lustrous, narrower, swollen dorsally. Fore femur (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1410,378,403]" captionStart="Figures 13-18" captionStartId="5.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[97,1416,991,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-354@5.[94,1417,986,2044]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 13-18: Fore femur of Macromalthinus species. (13) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (14) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov.(15) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(16) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(17) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(18) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384153/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) with a blunt tooth near apex, notched beyond apical fourth. Abdominal tergites and sternites broadly sclerotized; tergite VIII apically emarginated, distal angles prominent, forming a short conical projection; tergite IX as long as wide, asymmetrical, longer on its right side; ventrite VII (
<figureCitation box="[930,1007,570,595]" captionStart="Figures 19-24" captionStartId="6.[170,238,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[172,1491,1272,2042]" captionTargetId="figure-506@6.[170,1493,1269,2044]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 19-24:Ventrite VII of males of Macromalthinus species.(19) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(20) M.luteoapicalis sp.nov.(21)M. orapuensis sp.nov.(22) M.piceiventris sp.nov.(23) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(24) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384156/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) H-shaped, sides arched, with deep, wide membranous area anteriorly, and deep, wider posterior notch; ventrite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1144,634,659]" captionStart="Figures 25-30" captionStartId="7.[794,862,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[798,1414,205,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-491@7.[794,1418,204,1980]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 25-30: Ventrite VIII of males of Macromalthinus species. (25) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (26) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (27) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(28)M.piceiventrissp.nov.(29) M.quadratithoraxsp.nov.(30) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384158/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical,elongate, strongly convex; short and strong transverse lateral ridge near left margin, long and strong longitudinal ridge along right margin; distal surface densely pubescent. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[921,1000,762,787]" captionStart="Figures 31-36" captionStartId="8.[170,238,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[171,1491,674,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-183@8.[170,1493,670,2012]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 31-36: Aedeagus of Macromalthinus species. (31) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (32) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (33) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (34) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(35) M. quadratithorax sp.nov.(36) M. xerophilus sp.nov. Abbreviations:pt = prolongation of tegmen, sp = setiferous prolongation,rp = right paramere, lp = left paramere,ml = median lobe.Scale bars:0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384160/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) with right prolongation of tegmen narrow apically and markedly oblique, separated by a broad and straight notch from left setiferous prolongation; left setiferous prolongation elongate, slender, with few short apical setae; right paramere broad at base, rounded at apex; left paramere flat, wider at base, apex rounded, partially covering dorsal surface of median lobe; median lobe wider basally, broadly membranous apically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[894,1230,1018,1043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Measurements of 
<typeStatus box="[1116,1227,1018,1043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
TL: 8.9; AL: 5.9; HW: 1.34; IOW: 0.52; IAW: 0.17; OL: 0.68; PL: 0.98; PW: 1.1; EL: 1.84; EW: 1.3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[794,1418,1146,1299]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,988,1146,1171]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Female: Length:</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1000,1132,1146,1171]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="7.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="7.7">7.7-8.3 mm</quantity>
. Similar to light form of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Biffi &amp; Constantin" authorityYear="2018" box="[794,1100,1178,1203]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Macromalthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guyanensis">
<emphasis box="[794,1100,1178,1203]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Macromalthinus guyanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but elytra shorter. Ventrite VII (
<figureCitation box="[836,914,1210,1235]" captionStart="Figures 37-42" captionStartId="9.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[94,1414,1424,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-592@9.[94,1417,1420,2044]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 37-42:VentriteVII offemales ofMacromalthinusspecies.(37) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(38)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(39) M.orapuensissp.nov.(40)M.piceiventris sp.nov.(41) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(42) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384162/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) trapezoidal, longer, distal margin projected medially and notched at apex forming two small lobes; stylus of coxites (
<figureCitation box="[980,1055,1274,1299]" captionStart="Figures 43-48" captionStartId="10.[869,937,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[873,1490,1055,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-666@10.[869,1493,1054,1980]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 43-48: Coxites of Macromalthinus species. (43) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (44) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (45) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (46) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (47) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (48) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384164/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
) not constricted at base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
