<figureCitation box="[499,625,218,243]" captionStart="Figures 66-69" captionStartId="19.[94,162,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[151,1360,431,2012]" captionTargetId="figure-79@19.[151,1360,431,2012]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 66-69: Distribution of Macromalthinus species. (66) Distribution of Macromalthinus species in South America. (67) Distribution of M. brasiliensis in Brazil.(68)Distribution ofM.maximiceps inFrench Guiana.(69)Distribution of M.guyanensis sp.nov.,andM.orapuensis sp.nov.inFrench Guiana.Background maps of Figs.66-67 by NaturalEarth (available at:www.naturalearthdata.com), and Figs.68-69 byEric Gaba." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384172/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs. 66, 69</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[170,795,282,883]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[170,420,282,307]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Locality description:</emphasis>
The specimens were collected with malaise traps in peculiar natural zones of lowland swamp forests on hydromorphic soils at Crique Orfion and Petite Montagne Tortue. Both localities, southeastwards Cayenne along the National Road of the East to Régina, encompass a large number of protected plants and animals. Crique Orfion enjoys protection un- der Natural Zone of Ecological, Faunistic and Floristic Interest (ZNIEFF) station’s status. “Crique Orfion station with 
<taxonomicName box="[288,511,570,595]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Bactris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nancibaensis">
<emphasis box="[288,511,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Bactris nancibaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (endemic palm tree of the Guyanese littoral) includes over 3.000 hectares of drained forests, lowland swamp forests and swamp forests. Characteristic plants in the permanently flooded zones are 
<taxonomicName box="[282,459,698,723]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Euterpe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oleracea">
<emphasis box="[282,459,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Euterpe oleracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[471,589,698,723]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
) (‘pinot palm’,‘aÇaí palm’), 
<taxonomicName box="[249,492,730,755]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Clusiaceae" genus="Symphonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="globulifera">
<emphasis box="[249,492,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Symphonia globulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[502,623,730,755]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Clusiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Clusiaceae</taxonomicName>
) (‘chestick’,‘manil marécage’, ‘guanandi’) and especially 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lecythidaceae" genus="Lecythis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pneumatophora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Lecythis pneumatophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[313,476,794,819]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lecythidaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lecythidaceae</taxonomicName>
) (‘mahots’). In periodically exposed areas 
<taxonomicName authority="(Arecareae)" baseAuthorityName="Arecareae" box="[338,686,826,851]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Oenocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bataua">
<emphasis box="[338,552,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Oenocarpus bataua</emphasis>
(Arecareae)
</taxonomicName>
(‘patawa’, ‘patauá’) is quite abundant in the canopy (
<bibRefCitation author="Tostain, O." box="[633,785,858,883]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref19210" refString="Tostain, O. 2017. Biotope, Znieff 030030063, Stations a Bactris nancibaensis de la crique Orfion. Paris, INPN, SPN-MNHN. 7 p. Available at: https: // inpn. mnhn. fr / zone / znieff / 030030063. pdf. Access in: 14 / 03 / 2018." type="book" year="2017">Tostain, 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
